---
export const title = 'Usage';
export const order = 100;
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro'
---

<p>
  A Notion-like Markdown editor built on Tiptap. It supports four interaction
  patterns:
</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Slash commands</strong> — type <code>/</code> on any line to pick a block type from the menu.</li>
  <li><strong>Inline bubble toolbar</strong> — select text to reveal bold, italic, underline, strikethrough, and inline-code buttons.</li>
  <li><strong>Block handle</strong> — hover over any block to reveal a <code>+</code> button (insert a new block below) and a drag handle (reorder blocks by dragging).</li>
  <li><strong>Source toggle</strong> — the segmented switch at the bottom flips between the visual editor and the raw Markdown source; both views stay in sync.</li>
</ul>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-markdown-editor
    id="md-editor"
    label="Notes"
    helper-text="Type '/' · select text · hover a block for the +/drag handle"
    style="display:block;"
  ></wc-markdown-editor>
  <script is:inline>
    const mdEditor = document.getElementById('md-editor');
    mdEditor.addEventListener('change', () => {
      console.log('value changed:\n', mdEditor.value);
    });
  </script>
</DemoComponentCard>

<h2>Insert block</h2>

<p>
  Hover over any paragraph, heading, or other block to reveal a small handle
  panel to its left. Click the <strong>+</strong> button to open the block-type
  menu and insert a new block immediately below. The same block types are
  available as with the slash command.
</p>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-markdown-editor
    id="md-editor-insert"
    label="Project Brief"
    helper-text="Hover a block and click + to insert a new block below it."
    style="display:block;"
  ></wc-markdown-editor>
  <script is:inline>
    document.getElementById('md-editor-insert').value = [
      '## Goals',
      '',
      'Define the success criteria for this project.',
      '',
      '## Scope',
      '',
      'List what is in and out of scope.',
      '',
      '## Timeline',
      '',
      'Add milestones and deadlines here.',
    ].join('\n');
  </script>
</DemoComponentCard>

<h2>Drag to reorder</h2>

<p>
  Hover over a block and grab the drag handle (the six-dot icon) to drag the
  entire block to a new position. A drop cursor shows where the block will land.
</p>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-markdown-editor
    id="md-editor-drag"
    label="Agenda"
    helper-text="Hover a block, grab the drag handle, and drop it in a new position."
    style="display:block;"
  ></wc-markdown-editor>
  <script is:inline>
    document.getElementById('md-editor-drag').value = [
      '## Item 1 — Introductions',
      '',
      'Round-table introductions (5 min).',
      '',
      '## Item 2 — Status update',
      '',
      'Each team shares a 2-minute status.',
      '',
      '## Item 3 — Blockers',
      '',
      'Open floor for blockers and questions.',
      '',
      '## Item 4 — Next steps',
      '',
      'Assign owners and due dates.',
    ].join('\n');
  </script>
</DemoComponentCard>

<h2>Pre-filled content</h2>

<p>
  Set the <code>value</code> property to any Markdown string to pre-populate
  the editor. Toggle to the <strong>Markdown</strong> view to see the raw
  source; edits in either view stay in sync.
</p>

<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-markdown-editor
    id="md-editor-seeded"
    label="Release Notes"
    helper-text="Edits dispatch a 'change' event with the updated markdown."
    style="display:block;"
  ></wc-markdown-editor>
  <script is:inline>
    const seeded = document.getElementById('md-editor-seeded');

    seeded.value = [
      '# Release 1.0',
      '',
      'Welcome to **Peacock Markdown Editor** — a _Notion-like_ writing surface.',
      '',
      '## Highlights',
      '',
      '- Slash menu (`/`) for block insertion',
      '- Bubble menu for inline formatting',
      '- Block handle — hover to insert or drag-reorder blocks',
      '- Round-trips between visual and raw Markdown views',
      '',
      '> Tip: hover over any block to reveal the + and drag handle on the left.',
      '',
      '```js',
      'const editor = document.querySelector(\'wc-markdown-editor\');',
      'editor.value = \'# Hello world\';',
      '```',
      '',
      '---',
      '',
      'Happy writing!',
    ].join('\n');

    seeded.addEventListener('change', () => {
      console.log('release notes updated:\n', seeded.value);
    });
  </script>
</DemoComponentCard>
